From 217676c1029f93cba66331e0ef62ebf7b13bf744 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Abhinav Ayyapasetti <ayyapasetti.abhinav@windriver.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 2026 07:38:50 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Replace legacy facts and module variables for Puppet 8
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace deprecated top-scope fact variables with structured facts hash
and remove deprecated $:: prefix from module variables for Puppet 8.x
compatibility.

Changes include:
- $::osfamily → $facts['os']['family']
- $::operatingsystem → $facts['os']['name']
- $::operatingsystemmajrelease → $facts['os']['release']['major']
- $::operatingsystemrelease → $facts['os']['release']['full']
- $::hostname → $facts['networking']['hostname']
- $::fqdn → $facts['networking']['fqdn']
- $::service_provider → $facts['service_provider']
- $::lsbdistcodename → $facts['os']['distro']['codename']
- $::selinux → $facts['selinux']
- $::ceph:: → $ceph:: (44 instances)

This addresses Puppet 8 deprecation of top-scope variables and ensures
compatibility with modern Puppet versions.

Signed-off-by: Abhinav Ayyapasetti <ayyapasetti.abhinav@windriver.com>
